name: PRAMOD KUMAR B.
description:
Highly accomplished Snowflake Data Engineer with over 12 years of experience in databases, data warehousing, and data engineering, including a strong foundation in Oracle and PL/SQL. I hold a Snowflake SnowPro Core Certification and have a proven track record of designing robust, secure, and scalable data pipelines using the Snowflake ecosystem. I specialize in building end-to-end data engineering solutions that drive real-time insights and business automation. My hands-on expertise spans the modern data stack, including Fivetran for ingestion, dbt for transformation (where applicable), and Power BI for advanced analytics and visualization. I’m proficient in implementing CI/CD pipelines using Git to ensure streamlined development and deployment workflows.

Within the Snowflake platform, I have led performance optimization using clustering for micro-partition pruning, Query Acceleration Service (QAS), and search optimization. I’ve implemented multi-cluster warehouses to support high concurrency and used permanent, transient, and temporary tables as per use case. My experience includes leveraging Time Travel and Fail Safe, Dynamic Tables for overcoming materialized view limitations, and building flexible Power BI integrations. I have designed SCD Type 2 logic using Streams, Tasks, surrogate keys, and sequences, supported by thousands of lines of modular stored procedures and functions. I've managed secure data sharing with secure views, governed access via RBAC/DAC, applied Dynamic Data Masking and Row Access Policies, and enforced Network Policies for IP-level access control.

I’ve processed semi-structured data using VARIANT, FLATTEN, LATERAL FLATTEN, and Object_Construct, and handled data loading/unloading using COPY INTO, Snowpipe, SnowSQL, and internal/external stages. I’ve applied cost control using Resource Monitors and implemented Zero Copy Cloning for environment replication. Additionally, I’ve integrated Snowflake Cortex GenAI using LLM functions to automate SQL logic and stored procedure updates based on schema changes, and applied Cortex ML functions for in-platform forecasting and predictive modeling.

My broader experience includes data modeling using star and snowflake schemas, workflow orchestration using Python with Airflow and Kafka, and automation of manual processes using Python and VBA. Recognized for my strong communication, project leadership, and ability to deliver high-quality, scalable solutions on time and within budget, I also bring 18 months of on-site experience in the UK (Glasgow) working directly with clients in a senior Snowflake engineering capacity.

name: Thomas P.
description:
I am a data scientist who specializes in digital marketing analytics, Google Analytics 4 / Google Tag Manager, and customer behavioral analysis. 

I work primarily with e-commerce brands and B2Bs, but I also work with businesses in industries such as legal and professional services and real estate as well. 

I've recently completed GA4 projects for clients such as Vista Equity Partners, NASCAR, USAA, and AARP.

Web analytics tools, such as Google Analytics 4 and Google Tag Manager, play an indispensable role in today's business landscape. 

By tracking and analyzing user behavior, interaction patterns, and key performance indicators, these tools provide actionable insights that can drive decision-making and strategic planning. 

Understanding where visitors come from, what content they engage with, how they navigate through a site, and at what point they might leave, can uncover areas for optimization, allowing businesses to refine their marketing strategies, improve user experience, and increase conversion rates. 

Additionally, with real-time reporting, organizations can respond to trends quickly, adapting to market changes and maintaining a competitive edge. In an age where data-driven decisions are paramount to success, the investment in web analytics tools can often translate into increased revenue, customer retention, and overall business growth.

Google Analytics 4 (GA4) offers a host of advanced features and integrations that can provide valuable business intelligence to drive revenue. Here's how:

1. **Real-Time Data Analysis**: GA4's real-time reporting enables businesses to respond to trends and customer behaviors as they happen. This allows for immediate adjustments to marketing strategies or website content, ensuring optimal engagement and conversion.

2. **Audience Segmentation**: By understanding the different segments of an audience, businesses can create targeted marketing campaigns that resonate with specific groups. GA4's audience segmentation tools help identify these segments based on behavior, demographics, and interests, allowing for more personalized and effective marketing.

3. **Cross-Platform Tracking**: GA4's ability to track users across different devices and platforms gives a more holistic view of the customer journey. This can reveal insights into how different touchpoints influence purchasing decisions, enabling a more coordinated and efficient marketing approach.

4. **Predictive Metrics**: GA4 uses machine learning to offer predictive metrics, such as potential revenue from particular audience segments. This helps businesses to focus their efforts on the most promising areas, optimizing their return on investment.

5. **Enhanced Ecommerce Tracking**: By closely monitoring how users interact with products on a website, GA4 provides insights into which products are most appealing, the effectiveness of product recommendations, shopping cart abandonment rates, and more. This information is vital for optimizing product placement, pricing strategies, and overall ecommerce effectiveness.

6. **Integration with Advertising Platforms**: GA4's seamless integration with various advertising platforms, like Google Ads, means that businesses can manage and measure their advertising efforts within a unified environment. This ensures more precise targeting and measurement, driving a more efficient use of advertising budget.

7. **Custom Reporting and Dashboards**: GA4 allows for customized reporting that aligns with specific business goals and KPIs. This flexibility ensures that businesses have ready access to the most relevant data, empowering them to make informed decisions that align with their revenue-driving objectives.

8. **Compliance and Data Privacy**: With increased concerns over data privacy, GA4 has features to help businesses comply with regulations like GDPR. By maintaining compliance, businesses reduce the risk of legal issues that could impact revenue and reputation.

9. **Event Tracking and Automation**: GA4's event tracking capabilities allow businesses to understand user interactions at a granular level, such as clicks on specific buttons or form submissions. These insights can lead to the automation of specific responses, further optimizing user engagement and conversion pathways.

By leveraging these features, businesses can extract actionable insights, refine their strategies, and make data-driven decisions that align with their goals, ultimately leading to increased revenue.

name: Sergii K.
description:
Researcher and Data Scientist with PhD in Remote Sensing and 10+ years of academic/industrial experience. Participation in State and private research programs as a project head or an executive officer. Over fifteen years of successful research experience (h-index is 13, 90+ Scopus publications) in digital signal processing (1D and 2D signal processing including biomedical and physiological signal processing, preprocessing, filtering, compressing, visual quality) and data science. Strong problem-solving and analytical skills. Advanced programming proficiency. Certified in Data Analysis and Machine Learning by AWS, Coursera and Kaggle.

Skills:
Digital signal processing, Data mining, Data analysis, Statistics, Machine learning, Signal
filtering, Signal compressing, Python, SQL, GIT, MS VS Code,
Google Colab. Windows 10 + Linux (Debian, Ubuntu), basic AWS.

Python skills: 
numpy, pandas, scipy, matplotlib, plotly, seaborn, sklearn, scipy, pytorch, lightning, open-cv, biosppy, sqlalchemy, SQLite3, boruta, hyperopt, numba, xgboost, lightgbm etc.
Matlab skills: 
curve fitting, filter designer.

Professional stack:
•	Industrial researching (understanding of the business task; data evaluation: can the answer to this business task be hidden in them; collection of additional data if there is not enough to get an answer; the choice of the metric that most closely approximates the business goal; selection and construction model)
•	Scientific researching (purpose of the study, statement of the problem in general form, analysis of world achievements, research of a new method, conclusions, presenting result of research on international conferences)
•	Clinical trials (planning, conducting, analysis)
•	Exploratory data analysis (statistics on dataset, boxplots, range of categories etc.)
•	Data cleaning (missed values, category cleaning, category merging etc.)
•	Data preparation (category processing, projection of numbers into categories, transformation of numbers, binning, various scaling etc.)
•	Feature engineering (existing data-depended, current area-depended, using communication theory, using information theory etc.)
•	Feature selection (manual, brute-force, tree-based, grid, random)
•	Modelling (linear, kernel-based, tree-based, neural networks including deep networks)
•	Hyperparameter optimization (brute-force, grid, random, Bayesian)
•	Models validation (out-of-fold validation, cross-validation, holdout set validation)
•	Signals filtering (1D and 2D signals, Wavelet filters, DCT filters, FIR/IIR filters etc.)
•	Signals compressing (1D and 2D signals, lossless compression, lossy compression)

name: Thomas P.
description:
I am a data scientist who specializes in digital marketing analytics, Google Analytics 4 / Google Tag Manager, and customer behavioral analysis. 

I work primarily with e-commerce brands and B2Bs, but I also work with businesses in industries such as legal and professional services and real estate as well. 

I've recently completed GA4 projects for clients such as Vista Equity Partners, NASCAR, USAA, and AARP.

Web analytics tools, such as Google Analytics 4 and Google Tag Manager, play an indispensable role in today's business landscape. 

By tracking and analyzing user behavior, interaction patterns, and key performance indicators, these tools provide actionable insights that can drive decision-making and strategic planning. 

Understanding where visitors come from, what content they engage with, how they navigate through a site, and at what point they might leave, can uncover areas for optimization, allowing businesses to refine their marketing strategies, improve user experience, and increase conversion rates. 

Additionally, with real-time reporting, organizations can respond to trends quickly, adapting to market changes and maintaining a competitive edge. In an age where data-driven decisions are paramount to success, the investment in web analytics tools can often translate into increased revenue, customer retention, and overall business growth.

Google Analytics 4 (GA4) offers a host of advanced features and integrations that can provide valuable business intelligence to drive revenue. Here's how:

1. **Real-Time Data Analysis**: GA4's real-time reporting enables businesses to respond to trends and customer behaviors as they happen. This allows for immediate adjustments to marketing strategies or website content, ensuring optimal engagement and conversion.

2. **Audience Segmentation**: By understanding the different segments of an audience, businesses can create targeted marketing campaigns that resonate with specific groups. GA4's audience segmentation tools help identify these segments based on behavior, demographics, and interests, allowing for more personalized and effective marketing.

3. **Cross-Platform Tracking**: GA4's ability to track users across different devices and platforms gives a more holistic view of the customer journey. This can reveal insights into how different touchpoints influence purchasing decisions, enabling a more coordinated and efficient marketing approach.

4. **Predictive Metrics**: GA4 uses machine learning to offer predictive metrics, such as potential revenue from particular audience segments. This helps businesses to focus their efforts on the most promising areas, optimizing their return on investment.

5. **Enhanced Ecommerce Tracking**: By closely monitoring how users interact with products on a website, GA4 provides insights into which products are most appealing, the effectiveness of product recommendations, shopping cart abandonment rates, and more. This information is vital for optimizing product placement, pricing strategies, and overall ecommerce effectiveness.

6. **Integration with Advertising Platforms**: GA4's seamless integration with various advertising platforms, like Google Ads, means that businesses can manage and measure their advertising efforts within a unified environment. This ensures more precise targeting and measurement, driving a more efficient use of advertising budget.

7. **Custom Reporting and Dashboards**: GA4 allows for customized reporting that aligns with specific business goals and KPIs. This flexibility ensures that businesses have ready access to the most relevant data, empowering them to make informed decisions that align with their revenue-driving objectives.

8. **Compliance and Data Privacy**: With increased concerns over data privacy, GA4 has features to help businesses comply with regulations like GDPR. By maintaining compliance, businesses reduce the risk of legal issues that could impact revenue and reputation.

9. **Event Tracking and Automation**: GA4's event tracking capabilities allow businesses to understand user interactions at a granular level, such as clicks on specific buttons or form submissions. These insights can lead to the automation of specific responses, further optimizing user engagement and conversion pathways.

By leveraging these features, businesses can extract actionable insights, refine their strategies, and make data-driven decisions that align with their goals, ultimately leading to increased revenue.

name: Thomas P.
description:
I am a data scientist who specializes in digital marketing analytics, Google Analytics 4 / Google Tag Manager, and customer behavioral analysis. 

I work primarily with e-commerce brands and B2Bs, but I also work with businesses in industries such as legal and professional services and real estate as well. 

I've recently completed GA4 projects for clients such as Vista Equity Partners, NASCAR, USAA, and AARP.

Web analytics tools, such as Google Analytics 4 and Google Tag Manager, play an indispensable role in today's business landscape. 

By tracking and analyzing user behavior, interaction patterns, and key performance indicators, these tools provide actionable insights that can drive decision-making and strategic planning. 

Understanding where visitors come from, what content they engage with, how they navigate through a site, and at what point they might leave, can uncover areas for optimization, allowing businesses to refine their marketing strategies, improve user experience, and increase conversion rates. 

Additionally, with real-time reporting, organizations can respond to trends quickly, adapting to market changes and maintaining a competitive edge. In an age where data-driven decisions are paramount to success, the investment in web analytics tools can often translate into increased revenue, customer retention, and overall business growth.

Google Analytics 4 (GA4) offers a host of advanced features and integrations that can provide valuable business intelligence to drive revenue. Here's how:

1. **Real-Time Data Analysis**: GA4's real-time reporting enables businesses to respond to trends and customer behaviors as they happen. This allows for immediate adjustments to marketing strategies or website content, ensuring optimal engagement and conversion.

2. **Audience Segmentation**: By understanding the different segments of an audience, businesses can create targeted marketing campaigns that resonate with specific groups. GA4's audience segmentation tools help identify these segments based on behavior, demographics, and interests, allowing for more personalized and effective marketing.

3. **Cross-Platform Tracking**: GA4's ability to track users across different devices and platforms gives a more holistic view of the customer journey. This can reveal insights into how different touchpoints influence purchasing decisions, enabling a more coordinated and efficient marketing approach.

4. **Predictive Metrics**: GA4 uses machine learning to offer predictive metrics, such as potential revenue from particular audience segments. This helps businesses to focus their efforts on the most promising areas, optimizing their return on investment.

5. **Enhanced Ecommerce Tracking**: By closely monitoring how users interact with products on a website, GA4 provides insights into which products are most appealing, the effectiveness of product recommendations, shopping cart abandonment rates, and more. This information is vital for optimizing product placement, pricing strategies, and overall ecommerce effectiveness.

6. **Integration with Advertising Platforms**: GA4's seamless integration with various advertising platforms, like Google Ads, means that businesses can manage and measure their advertising efforts within a unified environment. This ensures more precise targeting and measurement, driving a more efficient use of advertising budget.

7. **Custom Reporting and Dashboards**: GA4 allows for customized reporting that aligns with specific business goals and KPIs. This flexibility ensures that businesses have ready access to the most relevant data, empowering them to make informed decisions that align with their revenue-driving objectives.

8. **Compliance and Data Privacy**: With increased concerns over data privacy, GA4 has features to help businesses comply with regulations like GDPR. By maintaining compliance, businesses reduce the risk of legal issues that could impact revenue and reputation.

9. **Event Tracking and Automation**: GA4's event tracking capabilities allow businesses to understand user interactions at a granular level, such as clicks on specific buttons or form submissions. These insights can lead to the automation of specific responses, further optimizing user engagement and conversion pathways.

By leveraging these features, businesses can extract actionable insights, refine their strategies, and make data-driven decisions that align with their goals, ultimately leading to increased revenue.

name: Thomas P.
description:
I am a data scientist who specializes in digital marketing analytics, Google Analytics 4 / Google Tag Manager, and customer behavioral analysis. 

I work primarily with e-commerce brands and B2Bs, but I also work with businesses in industries such as legal and professional services and real estate as well. 

I've recently completed GA4 projects for clients such as Vista Equity Partners, NASCAR, USAA, and AARP.

Web analytics tools, such as Google Analytics 4 and Google Tag Manager, play an indispensable role in today's business landscape. 

By tracking and analyzing user behavior, interaction patterns, and key performance indicators, these tools provide actionable insights that can drive decision-making and strategic planning. 

Understanding where visitors come from, what content they engage with, how they navigate through a site, and at what point they might leave, can uncover areas for optimization, allowing businesses to refine their marketing strategies, improve user experience, and increase conversion rates. 

Additionally, with real-time reporting, organizations can respond to trends quickly, adapting to market changes and maintaining a competitive edge. In an age where data-driven decisions are paramount to success, the investment in web analytics tools can often translate into increased revenue, customer retention, and overall business growth.

Google Analytics 4 (GA4) offers a host of advanced features and integrations that can provide valuable business intelligence to drive revenue. Here's how:

1. **Real-Time Data Analysis**: GA4's real-time reporting enables businesses to respond to trends and customer behaviors as they happen. This allows for immediate adjustments to marketing strategies or website content, ensuring optimal engagement and conversion.

2. **Audience Segmentation**: By understanding the different segments of an audience, businesses can create targeted marketing campaigns that resonate with specific groups. GA4's audience segmentation tools help identify these segments based on behavior, demographics, and interests, allowing for more personalized and effective marketing.

3. **Cross-Platform Tracking**: GA4's ability to track users across different devices and platforms gives a more holistic view of the customer journey. This can reveal insights into how different touchpoints influence purchasing decisions, enabling a more coordinated and efficient marketing approach.

4. **Predictive Metrics**: GA4 uses machine learning to offer predictive metrics, such as potential revenue from particular audience segments. This helps businesses to focus their efforts on the most promising areas, optimizing their return on investment.

5. **Enhanced Ecommerce Tracking**: By closely monitoring how users interact with products on a website, GA4 provides insights into which products are most appealing, the effectiveness of product recommendations, shopping cart abandonment rates, and more. This information is vital for optimizing product placement, pricing strategies, and overall ecommerce effectiveness.

6. **Integration with Advertising Platforms**: GA4's seamless integration with various advertising platforms, like Google Ads, means that businesses can manage and measure their advertising efforts within a unified environment. This ensures more precise targeting and measurement, driving a more efficient use of advertising budget.

7. **Custom Reporting and Dashboards**: GA4 allows for customized reporting that aligns with specific business goals and KPIs. This flexibility ensures that businesses have ready access to the most relevant data, empowering them to make informed decisions that align with their revenue-driving objectives.

8. **Compliance and Data Privacy**: With increased concerns over data privacy, GA4 has features to help businesses comply with regulations like GDPR. By maintaining compliance, businesses reduce the risk of legal issues that could impact revenue and reputation.

9. **Event Tracking and Automation**: GA4's event tracking capabilities allow businesses to understand user interactions at a granular level, such as clicks on specific buttons or form submissions. These insights can lead to the automation of specific responses, further optimizing user engagement and conversion pathways.

By leveraging these features, businesses can extract actionable insights, refine their strategies, and make data-driven decisions that align with their goals, ultimately leading to increased revenue.

Additionally, with real-time reporting, organizations can respond to trends quickly, adapting to market changes and maintaining a competitive edge. In an age where data-driven decisions are paramount to success, the investment in web analytics tools can often translate into increased revenue, customer retention, and overall business growth.

Google Analytics 4 (GA4) offers a host of advanced features and integrations that can provide valuable business intelligence to drive revenue. Here's how:

1. **Real-Time Data Analysis**: GA4's real-time reporting enables businesses to respond to trends and customer behaviors as they happen. This allows for immediate adjustments to marketing strategies or website content, ensuring optimal engagement and conversion.

2. **Audience Segmentation**: By understanding the different segments of an audience, businesses can create targeted marketing campaigns that resonate with specific groups. GA4's audience segmentation tools help identify these segments based on behavior, demographics, and interests, allowing for more personalized and effective marketing.

3. **Cross-Platform Tracking**: GA4's ability to track users across different devices and platforms gives a more holistic view of the customer journey. This can reveal insights into how different touchpoints influence purchasing decisions, enabling a more coordinated and efficient marketing approach.

4. **Predictive Metrics**: GA4 uses machine learning to offer predictive metrics, such as potential revenue from particular audience segments. This helps businesses to focus their efforts on the most promising areas, optimizing their return on investment.

5. **Enhanced Ecommerce Tracking**: By closely monitoring how users interact with products on a website, GA4 provides insights into which products are most appealing, the effectiveness of product recommendations, shopping cart abandonment rates, and more. This information is vital for optimizing product placement, pricing strategies, and overall ecommerce effectiveness.

6. **Integration with Advertising Platforms**: GA4's seamless integration with various advertising platforms, like Google Ads, means that businesses can manage and measure their advertising efforts within a unified environment. This ensures more precise targeting and measurement, driving a more efficient use of advertising budget.

7. **Custom Reporting and Dashboards**: GA4 allows for customized reporting that aligns with specific business goals and KPIs. This flexibility ensures that businesses have ready access to the most relevant data, empowering them to make informed decisions that align with their revenue-driving objectives.

8. **Compliance and Data Privacy**: With increased concerns over data privacy, GA4 has features to help businesses comply with regulations like GDPR. By maintaining compliance, businesses reduce the risk of legal issues that could impact revenue and reputation.

9. **Event Tracking and Automation**: GA4's event tracking capabilities allow businesses to understand user interactions at a granular level, such as clicks on specific buttons or form submissions. These insights can lead to the automation of specific responses, further optimizing user engagement and conversion pathways.

By leveraging these features, businesses can extract actionable insights, refine their strategies, and make data-driven decisions that align with their goals, ultimately leading to increased revenue.

I am committed to delivering exceptional results. My excellent time management skills and eagerness to learn ensure accurate, insightful analysis, compelling visualizations, and well-crafted reports.

Ready to optimize your data? Contact me today, and let’s achieve outstanding results together.

description:

Continuous Learning: The rapidly evolving field of data analytics motivates me to stay updated with the latest tools and techniques. I am committed to lifelong learning and adapting to new industry trends.

Experience:

I have spent more than 4years as a data analyst in multinational market and media research company Nielsen, and I have done several freelancing data analysis projects on different freelancing markets like Upwork, and Fiverr. 

I am passionate about the power of data to drive innovation and optimize business processes. I am actively seeking new opportunities where I can apply my analytical skills to solve real-world challenges and contribute to the success of dynamic organizations.

name: Alexandr N.
job_title: Machine Learning Engineer | Python, TensorFlow, OpenCV, PyTorch
description:
I’m a Machine Learning Engineer (Python) focused on Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and NLP with 7+ years of hands-on delivery. Typical results for clients: +5–20% model accuracy (better data/architecture/tuning), 30–60% lower inference latency (optimized pipelines, quantization, batching), and faster time-to-deploy (days → hours) with MLOps (Docker, CI/CD, model registries). I design reliable end-to-end ML systems: data pipelines, model training, evaluation, FastAPI services, and cloud deployment on AWS/GCP.

# Core stack (Machine Learning Engineer / Python):
 • Languages & libs: Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow/Keras, scikit-learn, OpenCV, NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, Matplotlib
 • Domains: Computer Vision (classification, detection, segmentation), NLP (text classification, NER, embeddings), Deep Learning (CNN, Transformers, GAN)
 • Serving & APIs: FastAPI, Flask, gRPC/REST, batch & real-time inference, ONNX/TensorRT (when applicable)
 • MLOps: Docker, GitHub Actions, MLflow/DVC, experiment tracking, model versioning, A/B & shadow deployments
 • Cloud & data: AWS (EC2/S3/Lambda/Batch/Elastic Beanstalk), GCP (Compute/Storage), PostgreSQL/MySQL, Redis, object storage
• Tooling: Jupyter/Colab, PyCharm/VS Code; Raspberry Pi/Arduino for edge PoCs when needed

# What clients hire me for:
 • End-to-end ML: data prep → model training (PyTorch/TensorFlow) → evaluation → API serving (FastAPI) → cloud deployment (AWS/GCP)
 • Computer Vision: OpenCV pipelines, CNN/Transformer models for classification, detection (YOLO/Detectron-style), segmentation; augmentation and post-processing
 • NLP: text classification, intent/NER, embeddings & semantic search; fine-tuning transformer models
 • Performance & cost optimization: vectorization, mixed precision, quantization, batch/stream inference, autoscaling
 • MLOps: Dockerized training & inference, CI/CD for models, MLflow/DVC experiment tracking, monitoring & rollbacks

# Selected outcomes:
 • Improved CV model accuracy +8–15% via better augmentation, loss functions, and hyper-parameter search
 • Cut inference latency 35–55% by moving to FastAPI, batching, and model quantization/ONNX
 • Reduced false positives 20–40% with better data curation and thresholding/calibration
 • Reduced monthly compute cost 25–45% by right-sizing instances and adding autoscaling

# How I work:
Scope → milestones → frequent demos. Clear baselines/metrics, reproducible experiments, reviewable code, and a clean handover (docs + Loom). Comfortable integrating with your DS team or owning the Machine Learning Engineer role end-to-end.

# Keywords:
Machine Learning Engineer, Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, Computer Vision, NLP, Deep Learning, Data Science, MLOps, FastAPI, REST API, AWS, GCP, scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy

name: Alexandr N.
job_title: Machine Learning Engineer | Python, TensorFlow, OpenCV, PyTorch
description:
I’m a Machine Learning Engineer (Python) focused on Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and NLP with 7+ years of hands-on delivery. Typical results for clients: +5–20% model accuracy (better data/architecture/tuning), 30–60% lower inference latency (optimized pipelines, quantization, batching), and faster time-to-deploy (days → hours) with MLOps (Docker, CI/CD, model registries). I design reliable end-to-end ML systems: data pipelines, model training, evaluation, FastAPI services, and cloud deployment on AWS/GCP.

# Core stack (Machine Learning Engineer / Python):
 • Languages & libs: Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow/Keras, scikit-learn, OpenCV, NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, Matplotlib
 • Domains: Computer Vision (classification, detection, segmentation), NLP (text classification, NER, embeddings), Deep Learning (CNN, Transformers, GAN)
 • Serving & APIs: FastAPI, Flask, gRPC/REST, batch & real-time inference, ONNX/TensorRT (when applicable)
 • MLOps: Docker, GitHub Actions, MLflow/DVC, experiment tracking, model versioning, A/B & shadow deployments
 • Cloud & data: AWS (EC2/S3/Lambda/Batch/Elastic Beanstalk), GCP (Compute/Storage), PostgreSQL/MySQL, Redis, object storage
• Tooling: Jupyter/Colab, PyCharm/VS Code; Raspberry Pi/Arduino for edge PoCs when needed

# What clients hire me for:
 • End-to-end ML: data prep → model training (PyTorch/TensorFlow) → evaluation → API serving (FastAPI) → cloud deployment (AWS/GCP)
 • Computer Vision: OpenCV pipelines, CNN/Transformer models for classification, detection (YOLO/Detectron-style), segmentation; augmentation and post-processing
 • NLP: text classification, intent/NER, embeddings & semantic search; fine-tuning transformer models
 • Performance & cost optimization: vectorization, mixed precision, quantization, batch/stream inference, autoscaling
 • MLOps: Dockerized training & inference, CI/CD for models, MLflow/DVC experiment tracking, monitoring & rollbacks

# Selected outcomes:
 • Improved CV model accuracy +8–15% via better augmentation, loss functions, and hyper-parameter search
 • Cut inference latency 35–55% by moving to FastAPI, batching, and model quantization/ONNX
 • Reduced false positives 20–40% with better data curation and thresholding/calibration
 • Reduced monthly compute cost 25–45% by right-sizing instances and adding autoscaling

# How I work:
Scope → milestones → frequent demos. Clear baselines/metrics, reproducible experiments, reviewable code, and a clean handover (docs + Loom). Comfortable integrating with your DS team or owning the Machine Learning Engineer role end-to-end.

# Keywords:
Machine Learning Engineer, Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, Computer Vision, NLP, Deep Learning, Data Science, MLOps, FastAPI, REST API, AWS, GCP, scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy

name: Alexandr N.
job_title: Machine Learning Engineer | Python, TensorFlow, OpenCV, PyTorch
description:
I’m a Machine Learning Engineer (Python) focused on Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and NLP with 7+ years of hands-on delivery. Typical results for clients: +5–20% model accuracy (better data/architecture/tuning), 30–60% lower inference latency (optimized pipelines, quantization, batching), and faster time-to-deploy (days → hours) with MLOps (Docker, CI/CD, model registries). I design reliable end-to-end ML systems: data pipelines, model training, evaluation, FastAPI services, and cloud deployment on AWS/GCP.

# Core stack (Machine Learning Engineer / Python):
 • Languages & libs: Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow/Keras, scikit-learn, OpenCV, NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, Matplotlib
 • Domains: Computer Vision (classification, detection, segmentation), NLP (text classification, NER, embeddings), Deep Learning (CNN, Transformers, GAN)
 • Serving & APIs: FastAPI, Flask, gRPC/REST, batch & real-time inference, ONNX/TensorRT (when applicable)
 • MLOps: Docker, GitHub Actions, MLflow/DVC, experiment tracking, model versioning, A/B & shadow deployments
 • Cloud & data: AWS (EC2/S3/Lambda/Batch/Elastic Beanstalk), GCP (Compute/Storage), PostgreSQL/MySQL, Redis, object storage
• Tooling: Jupyter/Colab, PyCharm/VS Code; Raspberry Pi/Arduino for edge PoCs when needed

# What clients hire me for:
 • End-to-end ML: data prep → model training (PyTorch/TensorFlow) → evaluation → API serving (FastAPI) → cloud deployment (AWS/GCP)
 • Computer Vision: OpenCV pipelines, CNN/Transformer models for classification, detection (YOLO/Detectron-style), segmentation; augmentation and post-processing
 • NLP: text classification, intent/NER, embeddings & semantic search; fine-tuning transformer models
 • Performance & cost optimization: vectorization, mixed precision, quantization, batch/stream inference, autoscaling
 • MLOps: Dockerized training & inference, CI/CD for models, MLflow/DVC experiment tracking, monitoring & rollbacks

# Selected outcomes:
 • Improved CV model accuracy +8–15% via better augmentation, loss functions, and hyper-parameter search
 • Cut inference latency 35–55% by moving to FastAPI, batching, and model quantization/ONNX
 • Reduced false positives 20–40% with better data curation and thresholding/calibration
 • Reduced monthly compute cost 25–45% by right-sizing instances and adding autoscaling

# How I work:
Scope → milestones → frequent demos. Clear baselines/metrics, reproducible experiments, reviewable code, and a clean handover (docs + Loom). Comfortable integrating with your DS team or owning the Machine Learning Engineer role end-to-end.

# Keywords:
Machine Learning Engineer, Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, Computer Vision, NLP, Deep Learning, Data Science, MLOps, FastAPI, REST API, AWS, GCP, scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy

name: Alexandr N.
job_title: Machine Learning Engineer | Python, TensorFlow, OpenCV, PyTorch
description:
I’m a Machine Learning Engineer (Python) focused on Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and NLP with 7+ years of hands-on delivery. Typical results for clients: +5–20% model accuracy (better data/architecture/tuning), 30–60% lower inference latency (optimized pipelines, quantization, batching), and faster time-to-deploy (days → hours) with MLOps (Docker, CI/CD, model registries). I design reliable end-to-end ML systems: data pipelines, model training, evaluation, FastAPI services, and cloud deployment on AWS/GCP.

# Core stack (Machine Learning Engineer / Python):
 • Languages & libs: Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow/Keras, scikit-learn, OpenCV, NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, Matplotlib
 • Domains: Computer Vision (classification, detection, segmentation), NLP (text classification, NER, embeddings), Deep Learning (CNN, Transformers, GAN)
 • Serving & APIs: FastAPI, Flask, gRPC/REST, batch & real-time inference, ONNX/TensorRT (when applicable)
 • MLOps: Docker, GitHub Actions, MLflow/DVC, experiment tracking, model versioning, A/B & shadow deployments
 • Cloud & data: AWS (EC2/S3/Lambda/Batch/Elastic Beanstalk), GCP (Compute/Storage), PostgreSQL/MySQL, Redis, object storage
• Tooling: Jupyter/Colab, PyCharm/VS Code; Raspberry Pi/Arduino for edge PoCs when needed

# What clients hire me for:
 • End-to-end ML: data prep → model training (PyTorch/TensorFlow) → evaluation → API serving (FastAPI) → cloud deployment (AWS/GCP)
 • Computer Vision: OpenCV pipelines, CNN/Transformer models for classification, detection (YOLO/Detectron-style), segmentation; augmentation and post-processing
 • NLP: text classification, intent/NER, embeddings & semantic search; fine-tuning transformer models
 • Performance & cost optimization: vectorization, mixed precision, quantization, batch/stream inference, autoscaling
 • MLOps: Dockerized training & inference, CI/CD for models, MLflow/DVC experiment tracking, monitoring & rollbacks

# Selected outcomes:
 • Improved CV model accuracy +8–15% via better augmentation, loss functions, and hyper-parameter search
 • Cut inference latency 35–55% by moving to FastAPI, batching, and model quantization/ONNX
 • Reduced false positives 20–40% with better data curation and thresholding/calibration
 • Reduced monthly compute cost 25–45% by right-sizing instances and adding autoscaling

# How I work:
Scope → milestones → frequent demos. Clear baselines/metrics, reproducible experiments, reviewable code, and a clean handover (docs + Loom). Comfortable integrating with your DS team or owning the Machine Learning Engineer role end-to-end.

# Keywords:
Machine Learning Engineer, Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, Computer Vision, NLP, Deep Learning, Data Science, MLOps, FastAPI, REST API, AWS, GCP, scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy

name: Alexandr N.
job_title: Machine Learning Engineer | Python, TensorFlow, OpenCV, PyTorch
description:
I’m a Machine Learning Engineer (Python) focused on Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and NLP with 7+ years of hands-on delivery. Typical results for clients: +5–20% model accuracy (better data/architecture/tuning), 30–60% lower inference latency (optimized pipelines, quantization, batching), and faster time-to-deploy (days → hours) with MLOps (Docker, CI/CD, model registries). I design reliable end-to-end ML systems: data pipelines, model training, evaluation, FastAPI services, and cloud deployment on AWS/GCP.

# Core stack (Machine Learning Engineer / Python):
 • Languages & libs: Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow/Keras, scikit-learn, OpenCV, NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, Matplotlib
 • Domains: Computer Vision (classification, detection, segmentation), NLP (text classification, NER, embeddings), Deep Learning (CNN, Transformers, GAN)
 • Serving & APIs: FastAPI, Flask, gRPC/REST, batch & real-time inference, ONNX/TensorRT (when applicable)
 • MLOps: Docker, GitHub Actions, MLflow/DVC, experiment tracking, model versioning, A/B & shadow deployments
 • Cloud & data: AWS (EC2/S3/Lambda/Batch/Elastic Beanstalk), GCP (Compute/Storage), PostgreSQL/MySQL, Redis, object storage
• Tooling: Jupyter/Colab, PyCharm/VS Code; Raspberry Pi/Arduino for edge PoCs when needed

# What clients hire me for:
 • End-to-end ML: data prep → model training (PyTorch/TensorFlow) → evaluation → API serving (FastAPI) → cloud deployment (AWS/GCP)
 • Computer Vision: OpenCV pipelines, CNN/Transformer models for classification, detection (YOLO/Detectron-style), segmentation; augmentation and post-processing
 • NLP: text classification, intent/NER, embeddings & semantic search; fine-tuning transformer models
 • Performance & cost optimization: vectorization, mixed precision, quantization, batch/stream inference, autoscaling
 • MLOps: Dockerized training & inference, CI/CD for models, MLflow/DVC experiment tracking, monitoring & rollbacks

# Selected outcomes:
 • Improved CV model accuracy +8–15% via better augmentation, loss functions, and hyper-parameter search
 • Cut inference latency 35–55% by moving to FastAPI, batching, and model quantization/ONNX
 • Reduced false positives 20–40% with better data curation and thresholding/calibration
 • Reduced monthly compute cost 25–45% by right-sizing instances and adding autoscaling

# How I work:
Scope → milestones → frequent demos. Clear baselines/metrics, reproducible experiments, reviewable code, and a clean handover (docs + Loom). Comfortable integrating with your DS team or owning the Machine Learning Engineer role end-to-end.

# Keywords:
Machine Learning Engineer, Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, Computer Vision, NLP, Deep Learning, Data Science, MLOps, FastAPI, REST API, AWS, GCP, scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy

name: Alexandr N.
job_title: Machine Learning Engineer | Python, TensorFlow, OpenCV, PyTorch
description:
I’m a Machine Learning Engineer (Python) focused on Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and NLP with 7+ years of hands-on delivery. Typical results for clients: +5–20% model accuracy (better data/architecture/tuning), 30–60% lower inference latency (optimized pipelines, quantization, batching), and faster time-to-deploy (days → hours) with MLOps (Docker, CI/CD, model registries). I design reliable end-to-end ML systems: data pipelines, model training, evaluation, FastAPI services, and cloud deployment on AWS/GCP.

# Core stack (Machine Learning Engineer / Python):
 • Languages & libs: Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow/Keras, scikit-learn, OpenCV, NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, Matplotlib
 • Domains: Computer Vision (classification, detection, segmentation), NLP (text classification, NER, embeddings), Deep Learning (CNN, Transformers, GAN)
 • Serving & APIs: FastAPI, Flask, gRPC/REST, batch & real-time inference, ONNX/TensorRT (when applicable)
 • MLOps: Docker, GitHub Actions, MLflow/DVC, experiment tracking, model versioning, A/B & shadow deployments
 • Cloud & data: AWS (EC2/S3/Lambda/Batch/Elastic Beanstalk), GCP (Compute/Storage), PostgreSQL/MySQL, Redis, object storage
• Tooling: Jupyter/Colab, PyCharm/VS Code; Raspberry Pi/Arduino for edge PoCs when needed

# What clients hire me for:
 • End-to-end ML: data prep → model training (PyTorch/TensorFlow) → evaluation → API serving (FastAPI) → cloud deployment (AWS/GCP)
 • Computer Vision: OpenCV pipelines, CNN/Transformer models for classification, detection (YOLO/Detectron-style), segmentation; augmentation and post-processing
 • NLP: text classification, intent/NER, embeddings & semantic search; fine-tuning transformer models
 • Performance & cost optimization: vectorization, mixed precision, quantization, batch/stream inference, autoscaling
 • MLOps: Dockerized training & inference, CI/CD for models, MLflow/DVC experiment tracking, monitoring & rollbacks

# Selected outcomes:
 • Improved CV model accuracy +8–15% via better augmentation, loss functions, and hyper-parameter search
 • Cut inference latency 35–55% by moving to FastAPI, batching, and model quantization/ONNX
 • Reduced false positives 20–40% with better data curation and thresholding/calibration
 • Reduced monthly compute cost 25–45% by right-sizing instances and adding autoscaling

# How I work:
Scope → milestones → frequent demos. Clear baselines/metrics, reproducible experiments, reviewable code, and a clean handover (docs + Loom). Comfortable integrating with your DS team or owning the Machine Learning Engineer role end-to-end.

# Keywords:
Machine Learning Engineer, Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, Computer Vision, NLP, Deep Learning, Data Science, MLOps, FastAPI, REST API, AWS, GCP, scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy

description:
I’m a Machine Learning Engineer (Python) focused on Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and NLP with 7+ years of hands-on delivery. I design reliable end-to-end ML systems: data pipelines, model training, evaluation, FastAPI services, and cloud deployment on AWS/GCP.

# Core stack (Machine Learning Engineer / Python):
 • Languages & libs: Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow/Keras, scikit-learn, OpenCV, NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, Matplotlib
 • Domains: Computer Vision (classification, detection, segmentation), NLP (text classification, NER, embeddings), Deep Learning (CNN, Transformers, GAN)
 • Serving & APIs: FastAPI, Flask, gRPC/REST, batch & real-time inference, ONNX/TensorRT (when applicable)
 • MLOps: Docker, GitHub Actions, MLflow/DVC, experiment tracking, model versioning, A/B & shadow deployments
 • Cloud & data: AWS (EC2/S3/Lambda/Batch/Elastic Beanstalk), GCP (Compute/Storage), PostgreSQL/MySQL, Redis, object storage
• Tooling: Jupyter/Colab, PyCharm/VS Code; Raspberry Pi/Arduino for edge PoCs when needed

# What clients hire me for:
 • End-to-end ML: data prep → model training (PyTorch/TensorFlow) → evaluation → API serving (FastAPI) → cloud deployment (AWS/GCP)
 • Computer Vision: OpenCV pipelines, CNN/Transformer models for classification, detection (YOLO/Detectron-style), segmentation; augmentation and post-processing
 • NLP: text classification, intent/NER, embeddings & semantic search; fine-tuning transformer models
 • Performance & cost optimization: vectorization, mixed precision, quantization, batch/stream inference, autoscaling
 • MLOps: Dockerized training & inference, CI/CD for models, MLflow/DVC experiment tracking, monitoring & rollbacks

# Selected outcomes:
 • Improved CV model accuracy +8–15% via better augmentation, loss functions, and hyper-parameter search
 • Cut inference latency 35–55% by moving to FastAPI, batching, and model quantization/ONNX
 • Reduced false positives 20–40% with better data curation and thresholding/calibration
 • Reduced monthly compute cost 25–45% by right-sizing instances and adding autoscaling

# How I work:
Scope → milestones → frequent demos. Clear baselines/metrics, reproducible experiments, reviewable code, and a clean handover (docs + Loom). Comfortable integrating with your DS team or owning the Machine Learning Engineer role end-to-end.

Machine Learning Engineer, Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, Computer Vision, NLP, Deep Learning, Data Science, MLOps, FastAPI, REST API, AWS, GCP, scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy
